# State Management Guidelines

## Core Concepts

- Use TanStack Router for URL-driven state
- Use TanStack Query for server state
- Use TanStack Form for form state
- Keep URL state clean and shareable
- Validate all URL parameters with Zod
- See [Core Concepts](mdc:.cursor/rules/core.mdc) for project setup
- See [Client Layer](mdc:.cursor/rules/client.mdc) for UI patterns

## URL State (TanStack Router)

### Basic Route with Search Params

```typescript
import { createFileRoute } from '@tanstack/react-router';
import { z } from 'zod';

const usersSearchSchema = z.object({
  page: z.coerce.number().default(1),
  sort: z.enum(['asc', 'desc']).default('desc'),
  filter: z.string().optional(),
});

export const Route = createFileRoute('/users')({
  validateSearch: usersSearchSchema,
  loader: ({ context: { queryClient }, search }) =>
    queryClient.ensureQueryData(
      queryOptions({
        queryKey: ['users', search],
        queryFn: () => $getUsers(search),
      }),
    ),
  component: UsersPage,
});
```

### Server State (TanStack Query)

```typescript
// Query with pagination
const useUsers = ({ page, sort }: { page: number; sort: 'asc' | 'desc' }) => {
  return useQuery({
    queryKey: ['users', { page, sort }],
    queryFn: () => $getUsers({ page, sort }),
  });
};

// Mutation with optimistic updates
const useUpdateUser = () => {
  return useMutation({
    mutationFn: (data: UpdateUserData) => $updateUser(data),
    onMutate: async (newUser) => {
      await queryClient.cancelQueries({ queryKey: ['user', newUser.id] });
      const previousUser = queryClient.getQueryData(['user', newUser.id]);
      queryClient.setQueryData(['user', newUser.id], newUser);
      return { previousUser };
    },
    onError: (err, newUser, context) => {
      queryClient.setQueryData(['user', newUser.id], context.previousUser);
    },
    onSettled: (data, error, variables) => {
      queryClient.invalidateQueries({ queryKey: ['user', variables.id] });
    },
  });
};
```

### Form State (TanStack Form)

```typescript
import { createForm } from '@tanstack/react-form';
import { z } from 'zod';

const userFormSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(2),
  email: z.string().email(),
});

function UserForm() {
  const form = createForm({
    defaultValues: {
      name: '',
      email: '',
    },
    onSubmit: async (values) => {
      await $createUser(values);
      toast.success('User created');
      navigate({ to: '/users' });
    },
  });

  return (
    <Form form={form}>
      <Field
        name="name"
        children={(field) => (
          <FormItem>
            <FormLabel>Name</FormLabel>
            <FormControl>
              <Input {...field.props} />
            </FormControl>
            <FormMessage>{field.error}</FormMessage>
          </FormItem>
        )}
      />
    </Form>
  );
}
```

### State Management Best Practices

1. URL State (TanStack Router)

   - Use for shareable state (pagination, filters, sort)
   - Always validate with Zod
   - Keep URLs clean and semantic
   - Handle invalid parameters gracefully

2. Server State (TanStack Query)

   - Use for remote data
   - Implement optimistic updates
   - Handle loading and error states
   - Use proper invalidation strategies

3. Form State (TanStack Form)

   - Use for all forms
   - Validate with Zod
   - Handle submission states
   - Implement proper error handling

4. Component State
   - Keep minimal
   - Use URL state when possible
   - Lift state up when needed
   - Use composition over prop drilling
